ly-Stage Growth Fund",12815,22403,"9.2",{"description":112,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":41,"endnote":113,"entity_id":114,"id":115,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":34,"income_type":47,"line_no":116,"metadata":47,"value_category_id":62,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"UK State Pension (value not readily ascertainable)","General governmental retirement system similar to Social Security.  The Filer is not currently eligible to start receiving payment at age 66 because he has not yet met the minimum 10 years of National Insurance contributions.",12816,22414,"10",{"description":32,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":118,"endnote":7,"entity_id":36,"id":119,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":11,"metadata":120,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},3,22418,"I hold vested restricted stock in Citigroup Inc. from my employment with Citibank, N.A. The vested restricted stock is restricted from sale until 8/20/2025. I will divest this stock not later than 90 days after my confirmation. (2022-02-01)",{"description":32,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":118,"endnote":7,"entity_id":36,"id":122,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":53,"metadata":123,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},22417,"I hold unvested restricted stock units (RSUs) with Citigroup Inc. from my employment with Citibank, N.A. A portion of my unvested RSUs were awarded for services that I provided when I was designated as a Material Risk Taker (MRT) under the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA) rules in the United Kingdom. Pursuant to the terms of Citigroup Inc.’s Discretionary Incentive and Retention Awards Plan (DIRA), upon my resignation and subject to regulatory approval from the PRA, Citigroup Inc. will accelerate the vesting of 75% of the unvested RSUs that were awarded when I was an MRT which will result in the issuance of stock in the company. I will forfeit the remaining 25% of my unvested RSUs that I was awarded when I was an MRT. If the PRA does not approve this treatment of my unvested RSUs, pursuant to the terms of the DIRA, Citigroup Inc. instead will convert 75% of the unvested RSUs that I was awarded when I was an MRT to a fixed amount of deferred cash compensation, and I will forfeit the remaining 25% of the unvested RSUs that I was awarded when I was an MRT. A portion of the deferred cash compensation will vest and be paid out each year with the final payment to occur in August 2028. Pursuant to the terms of the DIRA, Citigroup Inc. will accelerate the vesting of 75% of the unvested RSUs that were awarded when I was not an MRT which will result in the issuance of stock. The remaining 25% of the unvested RSUs that I was awarded when I was not an MRT will be forfeited at the time of my resignation. (2022-02-01)",{"description":32,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":118,"endnote":7,"entity_id":36,"id":125,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":61,"metadata":126,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},22416,"For services that I provided to Citibank N.A. in 2021, I am owed deferred compensation in the form of a fixed cash receivable. Pursuant to the terms of Citigroup Inc.’s DIRA, a portion of my remaining deferred cash compensation receivable will continue to vest each year on the pre-determined vesting schedule with the final payment occurring on 2/20/2027. (2021-02-01)",{"description":97,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":118,"endnote":7,"entity_id":98,"id":128,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":67,"metadata":129,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},22415,"There will be no further contributions to the pension plan from me or my employer following separation, but I will retain the ability to collect the pension when eligible according to existing terms. (2019-01-01)",{"description":131,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":118,"endnote":7,"entity_id":132,"id":133,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":75,"metadata":134,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Ernst & Young Pension",6104,22419,"I will retain the ability to collect the pension when eligible according to existing terms. (2012-10-01)",{"description":32,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":48,"endnote":7,"entity_id":36,"id":136,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":7,"line_no":11,"metadata":137,"value_category_id":7,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},22420,"Services as Managing Director, Independent Compliance Risk Management",{"description":139,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":45,"endnote":7,"entity_id":140,"id":141,"income_amount":59,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":142,"line_no":11,"metadata":7,"value_category_id":62,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Accenture (UK) Limited",69427,22422,"salary, bonus",{"description":144,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":45,"endnote":7,"entity_id":145,"id":146,"income_amount":59,"income_category_id":7,"income_type":47,"line_no":53,"metadata":7,"value_category_id":62,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Accenture PLC (employee purchase and restricted awards)",69428,22423,{"description":148,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":45,"endnote":7,"entity_id":149,"id":150,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":48,"income_type":46,"line_no":151,"metadata":7,"value_category_id":48,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Accenture stock",69429,22425,"2.1",{"description":153,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":45,"endnote":7,"entity_id":154,"id":155,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":34,"income_type":47,"line_no":156,"metadata":7,"value_category_id":118,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Accenture, unvested RSUs",69430,22426,"2.2",{"description":158,"appointee_id":33,"dsid":45,"endnote":7,"entity_id":159,"id":160,"income_amount":7,"income_category_id":34,"income_type":47,"line_no":161,"metadata":7,"value_category_id":41,"doc_id":14,"doc_url":15,"form_type":17},"Accenture (ESPP cash account)",69431,22421,"2.3",{